1) Partitioning in Spark is the process of dividing data into smaller chunks distributed across executors, enabling parallel processing and directly impacting performance and scalability 

rdd = spark.sparkContext.parallelize(range(10), 3)

print(rdd.getNumPartitions())  # Output: 3
⚙️ Types of Partitioning
🔹 1. Hash Partitioning

👉 Default in Spark
👉 Data distributed based on hash of key

🔹 2. Range Partitioning

👉 Data distributed based on value ranges

🔹 Repartition vs Coalesce
df = df.repartition(5)   # shuffle (increase/decrease)

df = df.coalesce(2)      # reduce partitions (no full shuffle)
⚡ Key Insight

👉
“Partitioning directly impacts performance because it controls how data is distributed and processed in parallel across the cluster.”

