Explanation

“In Apache Spark, bucketing is a data organization technique where data is divided into a fixed number of buckets based on a hash of a column, primarily used to optimize joins and queries.”

🔍 How it works

👉 Data is:

Hashed on a column (e.g., id)
Divided into fixed number of buckets
Stored physically in separate files
💻 Example
df.write \
  .bucketBy(4, "id") \
  .sortBy("id") \
  .saveAsTable("bucketed_table")
⚙️ Key Characteristics
Fixed number of buckets
Based on hash function
Data stored in structured format
⚡ Why Bucketing is Useful
🔹 1. Faster Joins

👉 If both tables are bucketed on same key
👉 Shuffle can be reduced

🔹 2. Efficient Querying

👉 Better data locality

🔹 Partitioning vs Bucketing
Feature	Partitioning	Bucketing
Basis	Column value	Hash function
Number	Dynamic	Fixed
Storage	Directory-based	File-based
Use case	Filtering	Joins
