3) Caching vs Persistence
✅ Definition

👉 In Apache Spark:

Cache → Stores data in memory only (default)
Persist → Stores data using different storage levels (memory, disk, etc.)
⚙️ Key Difference
Feature	Cache	Persist
Storage	Memory only	Memory / Disk / Both
Flexibility	❌ No	✔ Yes
Default	MEMORY_ONLY	User-defined
💻 Example
# Cache (default: MEMORY_ONLY)
df.cache()

# Persist (custom storage)
from pyspark import StorageLevel
df.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)
