5) Shuffle partition tuning involves adjusting the number of partitions used during shuffle operations to optimize parallelism and reduce execution time by balancing task size and overhead
# Default is 200
spark.conf.set("spark.sql.shuffle.partitions", "100")
=========================================================================

6) In Apache Spark, spark.sql.shuffle.partitions is a configuration parameter that defines the number of partitions created during shuffle operations like joins, groupBy, and aggregations.”

💻 Example
# Default value
spark.conf.get("spark.sql.shuffle.partitions")   # usually 200

# Change it
spark.conf.set("spark.sql.shuffle.partitions", "100")

