9) In Apache Spark, a broadcast hint is a directive given to Spark to force broadcasting of a DataFrame during a join, even if it does not automatically meet the broadcast threshold.”

💻 Example
from pyspark.sql.functions import broadcast

df1.join(broadcast(df2), "id").show()

👉 OR using SQL:

SELECT /*+ BROADCAST(df2) */
*
FROM df1
JOIN df2
ON df1.id = df2.id
🧠 Simple Scenario

👉 You have:

df_large → 10 GB
df_small → 50 MB

Spark might not auto-broadcast

Broadcast hint is used to explicitly instruct Spark to use broadcast join by distributing the smaller dataset to all executors, helping avoid shuffle and improve performance

