10) In Apache Spark, predicate pushdown is an optimization technique where filter conditions are pushed down to the data source level, so only the required data is read instead of scanning the entire dataset.”

💻 Example
df = spark.read.parquet("data.parquet")

# Filter applied
df.filter("age > 30").show()

👉 With predicate pushdown:

Filter is applied while reading data ✔
Not after loading everything

